'''Yama Shrine''' (やまじんじゃ) is a shrine in {{ill|lt=Hidaka-chō|Q5751503|WD=Q5751503|lt=Hidaka-chō|1=Hidaka, Hyōgo}}, {{ill|lt=Toyooka|Q696388|WD=Q696388|1=Toyooka, Hyōgo}}, {{ill|lt=Hyōgo Prefecture|Q130290|WD=Q130290|1=Hyōgo Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}), and its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}. It is one of the ten myōjin taisha in Tajima.

=== Overview ===
The Yama Shrine sacred grove, designated a city natural property, is magnificent, with giant Japanese magnolia trees growing across its broad precincts.

=== Enshrined deity ===
{{ill|lt=Kukunochi|Q10749920|WD=Q10749920|lt=Kukunochi-no-Mikoto|1=Kukunochi}} (くくのちのみこと)

=== About official shrines of Tajima Province ===
'Engishiki' 3 (Rinji-sai), myōjin festival article [28]

Myōjin festival, 285 seats. One seat at Awaga Shrine, two at Yabu Shrine, eight at Izushi Shrine.
One seat at Yama Shrine, one at To Shrine, one at Ikazuchi Shrine.
One seat at [木蜀]椒 Shrine, one at Kaijin Shrine.
All above are in Tajima Province.

=== Sessha and massha ===
Inari Shrine

=== Cultural property ===
Yama Shrine sacred grove - city designated natural property

=== Location information ===
; Location
:* Yamamiya 409-3, Hidaka-chō, Toyooka, Hyogo
; Transportation
:* Bus
:** From {{ill|lt=Ebara Station|Q871691|WD=Q871691|1=Ebara Station}} (JR West San'in Main Line), get off at Yamamiya ({{ill|lt=Zentan Bus|Q11389110|WD=Q11389110|1=Zentan Bus}} Kannabe Kōgen Line bound for Higashi-Kōchi), about 23 minutes, then 4 minutes on foot.
:* Car
:** From Nifu intersection on {{ill|lt=National Route 312|Q6157205|WD=Q6157205|1=Japan National Route 312}}, go west on {{ill|lt=National Route 482|Q6157664|WD=Q6157664|1=Japan National Route 482}}, about 14 minutes.

